§ Result ⦉
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ Let $x: Ω → 𝗥^d$ be a normally distributed random variable
    on a probability space $(Ω, 𝒜, 𝗣)$ with mean $μ ∈ 𝗥^d$ and
    covariance $Σ ≻ 0$. Let $g: 𝗥^d → 𝗥$ be the density of
    $x$. Then the entropy of $x$ is
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ h(g) = -∫g \log g = \frac{1}{2} \log ((2π e)^d \detΣ) ⦉
    ⦉⦉
</statement>
¶ ⦊
  ‖ This result tells us the ❬multivariate normal entropy❭ or
    ❬Gaussian entropy❭. ⦉
⦉

